defaultUK
default will need to balance this? Any idea?
defaultSir Jon defaultCunliffedefault: I do not have a number for that.
defaultTeresa Pearce:default Mr Sharp, do you have any idea?
defaultMr Sharpdefault: I think you are right that there is a supply problem. I do not know what the exact number is, but there is clearly a supply problem.
defaultTeresa Pearce:default But it is a big number.
defaultMr Sharpdefault: It is a very large number. If you look at the housing construction, it has been lamentable. If you look at the household formations, they are increasing significantly: people living longer, people living separately. If you look at the amount that is spent per household on housing in this country versus other countries, it is higher. There has been a supply problem.
defaultTeresa Pearce:default Dr Carney seemed to be intimating he knew the answer to the question there.
defaultDr Carneydefault: I do not know the answer to it, but I think I can give you a sense, which is very simple. As you know, I come from 
defaultCanada
default.
defaultTeresa Pearce:default Really?
defaultDr Carneydefault: It is still obvious, yes. There are roughly half as many people in 
defaultCanada
default as the 
defaultUK
