defaultUK
default, is hard touch from a financial stability perspective. A concern, which I know Andrew Bailey at the PRA and I certainly share, with the CRD IV compensation rules is that it takes back some of the advantages of the approach that we have had because it will incentivise more cash compensation today—exactly the type of problem we had before—that we cannot claw back. We would rather see more deferral, more equity, and this ability to take it back when those risks come to light.
